Croatia’s Agrokor Aims for Mercator Takeover, Dnevnik Reports

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-02-18T07:45:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/croatia-s-agrokor-aims-for-mercator-takeover-dnevnik-reports.html
Agrokor d.d., Croatia’s largest
privately held company, is readying a hostile takeover of
Slovenian retailer  Mercator Poslovni Sistem  d.d., Dnevnik
newspaper  reported , citing people from Croatia it didn’t name.  Agrokor will offer to acquire a 23.3 percent Mercator stake
that is being sold by Slovenia’s  Pivovarna Lasko  Group d.d. with
the aim to increase the stake to 50 percent, the Ljubljana-based
newspaper said.  Agrokor, which has tried to acquire Mercator in the past,
will also invite the European Bank for Reconstruction and
Development in its takeover bid for Mercator, according to
Dnevnik.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana, Slovenia, at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
